coalcamps.classes

Class CampLease

  • java.lang.Object
    • coalcamps.classes.CampLease
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public class CampLease
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Contains a POJO class annotated for ORM databases that represent a lease of a coal camp. Before the advent of automobiles entire towns, or coal camps, were built by mining companies to house miners. On occasion these towns and their associated mines were leased to other mining companies.

    This class is annotated to be used in a hibernate database. It consists of standard getter and setters, two constructors and an overridden toString routine. The standard getters and setters use Java Bean names, encapsulate private instance variables, have no side effects and are not further commented for purposes of brevity.

    Author:
    Mike Sheliga 3.15.18

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns all camp lease info including the foreign keys campLeased and companyBuilding. If the camp that was leased or the company building the camp is not set (likely due to lazy initialization) this information is not output.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
